parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A loose or cracked fuel filler neck/line can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, or accidents, especially when driving or refueling. Fuel leaks can also cause strong odors, discomfort, and health issues for occupants.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the filler neck or line
strong fuel odors inside or outside the vehicle
fuel sprays out of the A/C vents
fuel leaks when the tank is full or during cornering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can lead to the seat belt not holding the passenger in place, increasing the risk of injury or ejection in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle does not stay closed
the seat belt will not retract into the coil
the seat belt retractor is inoperative
the driver's front seat belt does not hold the passenger in the seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Brake Caliper and Parking Brake Design Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake caliper and parking brake design can cause the vehicle to fail to stop or lose control during panic stops, leading to accidents and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to stop or slows down inadequately during panic stops
the brakes feel soft or spongy
the rear wheels fail to lock or skid
the vehicle goes out of control during hard braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning proportioning/combination valve can cause the brakes to fail to distribute pressure evenly, leading to inadequate stopping power and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to stop or slows down inadequately during panic stops
the brakes feel soft or spongy
the rear wheels fail to lock or skid
the vehicle goes out of control during hard braking.
